{
  "stem": "4753.7",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there were many people who lived [INAUDIBLE] in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There were some who were not Jewish-- just their grandparents or one of their grandparents were Jew.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Had to come into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "These people were very angry toward us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They blamed us, that we are the reason they are in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They never thought about Hitler, who ordered these laws.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "These laws came always from the headquarters of the Nazi officers, and officers who went through the Jewish leaders, because they were the messengers.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had to walk there, wherever we had to go-- to the railroad station or to the ghetto or to the factory-- anywhere.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had to walk and carry our stuff, whatever we thought we need.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were the rabbis, the teachers, some doctors or lawyers, Jewish doctors and lawyers, who were appointed by the Germans to be the spokesmen for the Jewish people in the city.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were organizing the whole thing, telling us what to do, what to give to the Germans because, for example, we had to donate our bicycles, typewriters, radios if you had any.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father had a black little metal radio.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we had to give it in in the very few days after the occupation-- what were the very painful things because not only that was expensive to get it in the first place, but because my father was listening to it every single night, to the British Broadcasting Company.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that gave us some hope and some information about the war-- how is everything going?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But when we had to give it away, we had no feedback at all.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Up to that point, what kind of information had you been receiving?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What did you know of what was going on in other countries?",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
